• Telehealth: Explanation: Telehealth is limited to synchronous 2-way video-audio visits
Tier 1 - Zero Cost-Share Preventive Drugs: Explanation: 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 2 - Preferred Generic Drugs: Explanation: Value tier includes cost effective medications to treat chronic conditions. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 3 - Non-Preferred Generic Drugs: Explanation: Select tier includes certain cost effective brand medications. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 4 - Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Preferred medications are clinically effective at a favorable cost. Generic medications that have no more favorable outcomes, from a clinical perspective, than other more cost effective generic medications may be included in this tier. If using a brand medication when a generic equivalent is available, the member is responsible for the brand cost sharing plus the difference in cost between the generic and brand medication. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 5 - Non-Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Non-preferred brand medications that do not have significant therapeutic advantage over their preferred alternatives. These generally have safe and effective options available under the Value, Select and/or Preferred tiers. If using a brand medication when a generic equivalent is available, the member is responsible for the brand cost sharing plus the difference in cost between the generic and brand medication. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 6 - Preferred Specialty Drugs: Explanation: Preferred specialty medications are clinically effective at a favorable cost. Specialty medications often require special handling techniques, careful administration and a unique ordering process. Moda provides enhanced member services for these medications. Information about the clinical services and a list of eligible specialty medications is available on myModa or by contacting Customer Service. If a member does not purchase these medications at the exclusive specialty pharmacy, the expense will not be covered. Up to 30-day supply (per fill)

Standard On Exchange
• Telehealth: Explanation: Telehealth is limited to synchronous 2-way video-audio visits
Tier 1 - Zero Cost-Share Preventive Drugs: Explanation: 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 2 - Preferred Generic Drugs: Explanation: Value tier includes cost effective medications to treat chronic conditions. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 3 - Non-Preferred Generic Drugs: Explanation: Select tier includes certain cost effective brand medications. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 4 - Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Preferred medications are clinically effective at a favorable cost. Generic medications that have no more favorable outcomes, from a clinical perspective, than other more cost effective generic medications may be included in this tier. If using a brand medication when a generic equivalent is available, the member is responsible for the brand cost sharing plus the difference in cost between the generic and brand medication. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 5 - Non-Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Non-preferred brand medications that do not have significant therapeutic advantage over their preferred alternatives. These generally have safe and effective options available under the Value, Select and/or Preferred tiers. Tier 4 - Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Preferred medications are clinically effective at a favorable cost. Generic medications that have no more favorable outcomes, from a clinical perspective, than other more cost effective generic medications may be included in this tier. If using a brand medication when a generic equivalent is available, the member is responsible for the brand cost sharing plus the difference in cost between the generic and brand medication. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)
Tier 5 - Non-Preferred Brand Drugs: Explanation: Non-preferred brand medications that do not have significant therapeutic advantage over their preferred alternatives. These generally have safe and effective options available under the Value, Select and/or Preferred tiers. If using a brand medication when a generic equivalent is available, the member is responsible for the brand cost sharing plus the difference in cost between the generic and brand medication. 30-day supply standard retail; 90-day supply for retail 90 program/mail order (per fill)

Specialty medications often require special handling techniques, careful administration and a unique ordering process. Moda provides enhanced member services for these medications. Information about the clinical services and a list of eligible specialty medications is available on myModa or by contacting Customer Service. If a member does not purchase these medications at the exclusive specialty pharmacy, the expense will not be covered. Up to 30-day supply (per fill)
